12:05.423 --> 12:12.195
Ok, um. Does she
run away frequently?

12:12.197 --> 12:17.300
She runs off to the neighbors
without permission all the time.

12:17.302 --> 12:23.743
But I would not call
that running away.

12:24.208 --> 12:28.945
Ok, uhm...

12:28.947 --> 12:34.416
Thank you for your time.

12:34.418 --> 12:40.824
Well, government workers, right?

12:40.826 --> 12:47.966
So the father, is he around?

12:53.538 --> 12:59.943
I'm sorry. He died about...

12:59.945 --> 13:03.879
He died about five years ago.

13:03.881 --> 13:10.453
I'm sorry. I could really
use him right about now.

13:10.455 --> 13:12.387
I'm sorry.

13:12.389 --> 13:16.158
Don't worry about it.

13:16.160 --> 13:19.462
Who were your neighbors again?

13:19.464 --> 13:22.531
Uhm, the Young's.

13:22.533 --> 13:25.234
Can I get you to write
down their address for us?

13:25.236 --> 13:30.909
Of course.

13:37.448 --> 13:40.282
What about school?

13:40.284 --> 13:48.023
Uh, Southside.
That's were she met Jane.

13:48.025 --> 13:50.959
And what exactly do
you do at the racetrack?

13:50.961 --> 13:54.664
Uhm well I help keep
the books there.

13:54.666 --> 14:00.036
And uh pretty
much stock the concession stand

14:00.038 --> 14:03.105
And check on the racers the
night of the race, and make sure

14:03.107 --> 14:04.574
