for Halley Dawn's teacher.

23:09.953 --> 23:13.189
ETHAN: Huh, yup that would be me.
Uhm, Flynn.

23:13.191 --> 23:14.722
Is that your first name?

23:14.724 --> 23:20.496
No, sorry. First
name is Ethan.

23:20.498 --> 23:21.697
Mr. Flynn, we
wanted to ask you a few

23:21.699 --> 23:26.501
questions about Halley Dawn.
She went missing this morning.

23:26.503 --> 23:30.538
Oh God.
Uh, that's... that's terrible.

23:30.540 --> 23:32.874
Yea, what what did, uh what did
ya... what do you want to know?

23:32.876 --> 23:34.610
You know, did she
get along with everybody?

23:34.612 --> 23:36.511
Did you see anything strange?

23:36.513 --> 23:40.082
Or maybe her mom had
some weirdos come by?

23:40.084 --> 23:44.119
No, no, nothing...
nothing like that.

23:44.121 --> 23:46.055
Can you think
of anything?

23:46.057 --> 23:50.124
Um, well a lot of
times her friend's parents will

23:50.126 --> 23:52.260
pick her up and drop her off.

23:52.262 --> 23:53.027
The Young's?

23:53.029 --> 23:54.630
- Yes.
- Okay,

23:54.632 --> 23:57.132
And generally that means
that the mom works a lot.

23:57.134 --> 24:01.737
Um which means that she's not
as engaged in the child's life.

24:01.739 --> 24:04.672
Which then reflects on
the child's school life.

24:04.674 --> 24:06.709
How's that?

24:06.711 --> 24:09.644
Well she is probably
the quietest student I have.

24:09.646 --> 24:11.080
But the kids are still
really nice to her,

24:11.082 --> 24:12.315
surprisingly enough.

24:12.317 --> 24:14.917
You know she does her work, she
keeps her head down and stays

24:14.919 --> 24:16.552
out of trouble.

24:16.554 --> 24:17.719
You ever see her mom?

24:17.721 --> 24:21.824
Yea, yea. Uh, I mean... you
know for like the mandatory

24:21.826 --> 24:24.559
parent/teacher type things.

24:24.561 --> 24:27.095
Would you describe
her as a good mom?

24:27.097 --> 24:29.532
I don't think that I know her
well enough to speak on her

24:29.534 --> 24:33.235
character. Um you can really
only really judge a parent on

24:33.237 --> 24:39.307
their child's grades.
And for Halley, uhm, well...

24:39.309 --> 24:42.811
her grades were
through the roof.

24:42.813 --> 24:44.145
You seemed a little
hesitant on that.

24:44.147 --> 24:48.717
Well, for a student
to have the grades that Halley

24:48.719 --> 24:52.086
does, it usually means that the
parent is much more involved in

24:52.088 --> 24:52.988
her life.

24:52.990 --> 24:56.959
What about family
friends or boyfriends.

24:56.961 --> 25:01.596
I remember a guy dropping
her mom off a couple times

25:01.598 --> 25:03.632
for the parent teacher
things she did.

25:03.634 --> 25:05.066
Do you know who?

25:05.068 --> 25:09.837
No, I'm sorry.
Unfortunately I don't.

25:09.839 --> 25:13.609
Do you remember Halley saying
anything that stood out to you?

25:13.611 --> 25:18.581
I remember her talking about
doing homework at her house

25:18.583 --> 25:21.717
and at her mom's work.

25:21.719 --> 25:26.087
Excuse me for one moment.

25:26.089 --> 25:28.591
Study hall? At the racetrack?

25:28.593 --> 25:29.592
Yea we should go there now.

25:29.594 --> 25:30.625
Yup.

25:30.627 --> 25:33.629
I'm sorry, did you
say racetrack?

25:33.631 --> 25:34.729
Mrs. Dawn works there.

25:34.731 --> 25:39.602
Oh really? I... I had no idea.

25:39.604 --> 25:41.103
You ever go to the racetrack?

25:41.105 --> 25:46.307
Me? No, sorry,
that's not... not for me.

25:46.309 --> 25:49.944
- Thank you.
- Thank you for your time.

25:49.946 --> 25:54.952
♪ LIGHT PIANO
MUSIC ENSUES ♪

26:18.041 --> 26:20.845
[BIRDS CAWING SOUND EFFECT]

26:21.378 --> 26:28.319
Why don't you take
the lead on this one.

26:33.356 --> 26:37.825
CLAYTON: Sorry we don't uh... we don't
open again for another uh... 5 hours

26:37.827 --> 26:38.826
or so.

26:38.828 --> 26:41.063
We're looking for
Maddie Dawn. Is she here?

26:41.065 --> 26:42.831
Yea she's out
back. What's this about?

26:42.833 --> 26:44.199
We just need to ask
her a few questions.

26:44.201 --> 26:46.134
I'm detective Shepherd
and this is detective Willow.

26:46.136 --> 26:49.270
Ok, well, yea she's here. Is
here anything I should know

26:49.272 --> 26:50.773
about?

26:50.775 --> 26:52.074
You know anything
about this track?

26:52.076 --> 26:53.676
I own it.

26:53.678 --> 26:56.077
Oh, you're Mr. Woods?

26:56.079 --> 26:57.813
You must have been
asking around.

26:57.815 --> 26:59.815
Yea we talked to
Maddie earlier today.

26:59.817 --> 27:02.151
You have any
contact outside of work?

27:02.153 --> 27:03.818
Some.
What's this about?

27:03.820 --> 27:07.189
We're just trying to
see if you've seen her daughter.

27:07.191 --> 27:08.423
Halley's missing?

27:08.425 --> 27:11.826
You know her?

27:11.828 --> 27:14.162
Yea I'd try to be
nice to her at those parties.

27:14.164 --> 27:16.431
You know, felt bad for her.

27:16.433 --> 27:17.600
Why is that?

27:17.602 --> 27:20.334
Well her mama seemed too
distracted, you know, to really

27:20.336 --> 27:21.804
be a mama.

27:21.806 --> 27:25.440
So you had contact with Halley?

27:25.442 --> 27:28.744
No more than anybody
else at those parties.

27:28.746 --> 27:31.913
What happens at those
racetrack parties?

27:31.915 --> 27:33.449
Well Maddie would
invite everybody over.

27:33.451 --> 27:37.318
Racers, staff, me. We'd sit
around listen to music, drink

27:37.320 --> 27:39.121
beer. Nothing too wild.

27:39.123 --> 27:40.855
Any boyfriends?

27:40.857 --> 27:43.392
I try not to dabble too much,
but she didn't seem to have much

27:43.394 --> 27:45.294
luck with the guys.

27:45.296 --> 27:48.229
Some would say that
you two were a couple.

27:48.231 --> 27:52.468
Yea, well, you know.
Off and on every now and again.

27:52.470 --> 27:55.738
Right now I think I'd describe
us as being on a break.

27:55.740 --> 27:56.904
Mind if we talk to Maddie?

27:56.906 --> 28:00.976
No. Go right ahead.

28:00.978 --> 28:07.749
♪ PIANO MUSIC CONTINUES ♪

28:07.751 --> 28:12.019
[INDISTINCTIVE
CHATTER CAN BE HEARD]

28:12.021 --> 28:17.028
♪ PIANO MUSIC CONTINUES ♪

28:37.515 --> 28:40.815
Moving?

28:40.817 --> 28:42.351
DUNCAN:
Wish I was.

28:42.353 --> 28:44.385
Somewhere we're
it wasn't balls-hot.

28:44.387 --> 28:46.921
Can I help you?

28:46.923 --> 28:51.125
Sure I guess.

28:51.127 --> 28:52.894
What do you do around here?

28:52.896 --> 28:59.901
I race. Work on the cars.
Do odd jobs around the track.

28:59.903 --> 29:02.304
You know Maddie Dawn?

29:02.306 --> 29:04.405
Yup.

29:04.407 --> 29:07.809
Have any opinions about her?

29:07.811 --> 29:10.344
Yea, but there about the same as
what I think about the rest of

29:10.346 --> 29:13.981
the trash that
works around here.

29:13.983 --> 29:15.551
Truman Duncan.

29:15.553 --> 29:18.085
Detective Willow.

29:18.087 --> 29:19.388
That's not good.

29:19.390 --> 29:21.222
Why?

29:21.224 --> 29:24.526
Don't meet too many detectives.
I assume something bad has

29:24.528 --> 29:25.460
happened.

29:25.462 --> 29:28.896
A lot of bad things
happen around here?

29:28.898 --> 29:32.934
Just the usual.
Drunks, wrecks, fights, checks

29:32.936 --> 29:39.941
bouncing. Nothing to feed my
adrenaline addiction.

29:39.943 --> 29:41.076
Bad joke.

29:41.078 --> 29:43.845
To answer your question,
we're here to help Mrs. Dawn.

29:43.847 --> 29:46.547
Help? In what way?

29:46.549 --> 29:53.055
Halley seems to
have gone missing.

29:53.057 --> 29:54.389
I don't know anything.

29:54.391 --> 29:56.959
People around here
don't really like to talk.

29:56.961 --> 29:58.459
Unless it's about cheating on
their wives with the new

29:58.461 --> 30:02.965
secretary or dealing
drugs down at the truck stop.

30:02.967 --> 30:06.267
You ever talk to Halley?

30:06.269 --> 30:09.604
She is a good kid.
I think she knows she doesn't

30:09.606 --> 30:13.475
have it very good. Smart for a
kid to see that, my kid was like

30:13.477 --> 30:19.918
that. You're partner
is looking for you.

30:31.528 --> 30:32.494
Who was that?

30:32.496 --> 30:35.631
He works here.

30:35.633 --> 30:36.968
Anything?

30:37.999 --> 30:40.904
Nothing.

30:42.640 --> 30:46.511
We're still working
on some things.

30:48.311 --> 30:54.949
Found this in here.
I had to force her to wear it.

30:54.951 --> 31:00.622
I knew she wouldn't want to.
I didn't want her to get cold.

31:00.624 --> 31:04.092
Did Halley come here a lot?

31:04.094 --> 31:09.530
Yea. It was cheaper
than getting a babysitter.

31:09.532 --> 31:14.338
Is this really the
safest place for a little girl?

31:19.076 --> 31:22.881
Is any place?

31:24.682 --> 31:28.517
What's the next step?

31:28.519 --> 31:32.120
Well there'll be a press
conference and uh, it would be

31:32.122 --> 31:35.222
good if you were there.

31:35.224 --> 31:37.526
You said that your daughter used
to sneak off to your neighbors

31:37.528 --> 31:39.361
a lot.

31:39.363 --> 31:42.497
She may have just ran away
and is still hiding out.

31:42.499 --> 31:49.971
Maybe. She was mad
at me about something.

31:49.973 --> 31:52.708
If I could go back in time, I
would tell myself to

31:52.710 --> 31:59.381
be more patient with her.

31:59.383 --> 32:06.188
You try to do the
best you can, but it's hard.

32:06.190 --> 32:13.228
Sometimes you do or say
things you don't mean to.

32:13.230 --> 32:15.697
Nobody gives you any
instructions on how to be a

32:15.699 --> 32:23.341
parent, especially by yourself.

32:29.012 --> 32:31.712
TV:
Hello? [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

32:31.714 --> 32:38.085
You know.
I can't think of anyone else.

32:38.087 --> 32:44.226
Nobody really sticks
out in my mind.

32:44.228 --> 32:47.496
What do you think?

32:47.498 --> 32:50.532
I don't want to
talk about the case.

32:50.534 --> 32:53.735
I'll talk about anything
else other than the case.

32:53.737 --> 33:01.642
Alright. How about
some baseball.

33:01.644 --> 33:07.649
What? What made you
want to be a cop?

33:07.651 --> 33:13.455
I'm serious, what made
you want to do this?

33:13.457 --> 33:14.789
You wanted to talk about
something else, this is

33:14.791 --> 33:20.461
something else.

33:20.463 --> 33:25.600
After school, I needed a job.

33:25.602 --> 33:30.475
I met a recruiter. It was a job.

33:31.208 --> 33:34.379
Jesus.

33:37.413 --> 33:41.682
Why are you
so closed off? Why?

33:41.684 --> 33:47.655
You know life isn't as
bad as you make it out to be.

33:47.657 --> 33:55.165
Everything is a fight with you
right now. I'm not the enemy.

34:01.305 --> 34:03.305
I'm sorry your about
your dad passing, ok?

34:03.307 --> 34:06.440
I know it's been a rough year.

34:06.442 --> 34:14.085
It's like you've quit,
on everything.

34:20.190 --> 34:24.295
He wanted me to be a cop.

34:26.130 --> 34:30.601
At least, he always talked about
how much he admired them.

34:31.168 --> 34:33.135
We'd go to parades and
stuff, and he'd say

34:33.137 --> 34:35.637
"look at them, they get to
protect people and take care of

34:35.639 --> 34:39.907
people and make sure nothing bad
ever happens to anyone" and...

34:39.909 --> 34:46.780
At least, that's what I thought
he said when I was a kid.

34:46.782 --> 34:49.751
He didn't think there was
anything higher than being

34:49.753 --> 34:52.623
an officer.

34:56.626 --> 35:04.335
And I just wanted to do anything
I could to make him proud.

35:11.574 --> 35:14.708
What are you doing?

35:14.710 --> 35:17.512
I'm gonna get coffee.

35:17.514 --> 35:19.213
At this hour?

35:19.215 --> 35:25.889
Or a snack, a
magazine, a movie, whatever.

35:38.335 --> 35:40.969
Detective Willow.

35:40.971 --> 35:42.938
Mr. Woods.

35:42.940 --> 35:44.305
How's it going?

35:44.307 --> 35:47.474
Uh, filling up,
same as you.

35:47.476 --> 35:50.478
No I meant uh... with Halley.

35:50.480 --> 35:52.813
I mean I know this ain't some-
thing that a police officer

35:52.815 --> 35:54.416
wants to deal with,
you know I just...

35:54.418 --> 35:58.220
Um, yea I can't
really talk about the case but I

35:58.222 --> 35:59.287
appreciate you asking.

35:59.289 --> 36:01.356
You know what, I'm
so sorry, let me rephrase that.

36:01.358 --> 36:04.325
Is there anyway I can help, I
mean I've known Maddie forever.

36:04.327 --> 36:07.729
- We've had our ups and downs...
- Yeah, sure, sure. honestly just...

36:07.731 --> 36:11.435
Keep an eye out for anything
unusual at the track?

36:12.436 --> 36:15.970
Cases like these she's
probably just real close.

36:15.972 --> 36:17.206
Yeah.

36:17.208 --> 36:21.976
We just need evidence to find
her. She probably just ran away.

36:21.978 --> 36:26.347
You know what, let's hope so.

36:26.349 --> 36:28.349
Well, have a good one.

36:28.351 --> 36:31.955
I've go t to prepay
in here. Haha.

36:54.945 --> 37:04.956
♪ Suspenseful Music ♪

37:39.922 --> 37:47.028
Yesterday was uh...
yesterday was rough.

37:47.030 --> 37:50.735
First day usually is.

37:56.472 --> 38:00.844
You hear me?

38:04.847 --> 38:12.954
And um, I could... I could give
you... give you a thousand reasons

38:12.956 --> 38:15.892
why this is happening.

38:19.963 --> 38:22.967
I could tell you it was
just for the money.

38:27.570 --> 38:30.940
I could tell you...

38:31.942 --> 38:36.378
I could tell you I was
abused as a kid. You know.

38:36.380 --> 38:42.952
And that uh, my stepdad
used to knock me around and...

38:45.956 --> 38:49.523
and that I spent my childhood
trying to find out where my

38:49.525 --> 38:56.998
power was and
were my power disappeared to.

38:57.000 --> 38:59.666
And that the only reason I'm
even doing this is to get that

38:59.668 --> 39:09.144
power back, that
I lost as a kid.

39:09.146 --> 39:13.414
But none of that would
really matter, I don't think.

39:13.416 --> 39:17.418
I think all that really
matters right now is that you

39:17.420 --> 39:22.624
just need to accept that
this is happening.

39:22.626 --> 39:27.461
And that there's nothing you can
do about it. And that you just

39:27.463 --> 39:31.434
need to settle into it.

39:35.438 --> 39:39.441
The only thing you really need
to remember about any of this

39:39.443 --> 39:46.684
is that I'm in charge,
and what I say goes.

39:54.023 --> 39:59.028
And that that man right
over there in that red truck...

40:01.864 --> 40:09.406
is paying with
cash and he's paying today.

40:10.106 --> 40:18.516
♪ INTENSE CINEMATIC
MUSIC CONTINUES ♪

40:47.610 --> 40:50.077
How did it go yesterday?

40:50.079 --> 40:51.646
You heard?

40:51.648 --> 40:56.650
Yea, it was in the
paper. It's such a shame.

40:56.652 --> 41:00.688
Yea. No... no luck.

41:00.690 --> 41:03.925
Well I'm sure
something will turn up.

41:03.927 --> 41:07.128
Yeah, me too.

41:07.130 --> 41:08.795
How was your day yesterday?

41:08.797 --> 41:13.034
Didn't do a whole lot.
Just ran some errands.

41:13.036 --> 41:19.543
I do manage to
stay busy without you, you know.

41:25.282 --> 41:32.756
I miss eating with
him. I miss his laugh.

41:37.760 --> 41:46.202
[LAUGHING SOUNDS ENSUE]

41:50.206 --> 41:55.980
I'll always remember that laugh.

42:00.050 --> 42:02.249
I just can't get to a point
in my day where I don't

42:02.251 --> 42:08.592
miss him.

42:09.826 --> 42:14.628
How are you ok?

42:14.630 --> 42:19.733
You think I'm ok?
Honey I miss your dad more than

42:19.735 --> 42:25.238
you'll ever know.

42:25.240 --> 42:30.713
I miss... him.

42:35.150 --> 42:38.920
But hope is still there.

42:38.922 --> 42:41.655
Thank you.

42:41.657 --> 42:44.228
You have to fight for that.

42:46.228 --> 42:53.166
For hope.

42:53.168 --> 42:58.576
What are you fighting for today?

43:05.849 --> 43:08.215
How's your mom?

43:08.217 --> 43:12.623
Enlightening.

43:32.074 --> 43:36.411
Does this work?

43:36.413 --> 43:38.916
Yea.

43:42.351 --> 43:45.420
Captain wants a
press conference.

43:45.422 --> 43:47.921
When?

43:47.923 --> 43:50.358
After lunch.

43:50.360 --> 43:52.695
Ok.

43:57.467 --> 43:59.066
[DOOR KNOCKING SOUND EFFECT]

43:59.068 --> 44:00.333
Detective?

44:00.335 --> 44:01.903
Yea?

44:01.905 --> 44:03.403
Olivia Peterson, we-

44:03.405 --> 44:07.407
Yes I remember.

44:07.409 --> 44:10.945
Oh. I was wondering
if you had any information on...

44:10.947 --> 44:14.652
No, none at all.

44:15.018 --> 44:21.090
We talked to all the people who
knew her best, but you know...

44:23.358 --> 44:29.731
Well, maybe she did
run away, but still...

44:29.733 --> 44:32.967
I know that you're
just trying to be helpful. Um...

44:32.969 --> 44:35.036
if we have anything
we will let you know.

44:35.038 --> 44:36.804
Is this your first time?

44:36.806 --> 44:42.342
What? Working
with cops? No.

44:42.344 --> 44:47.481
I meant a missing
persons case.

44:47.483 --> 44:51.885
Yes.

44:51.887 --> 44:55.356
A friend of mine worked
one in the county over.

44:55.358 --> 44:57.992
The girl went missing,
and she brought some of us over

44:57.994 --> 45:05.499
as council. We tried to help but
she turned out to be a runaway.

45:05.501 --> 45:13.407
We did find her though, in a
ditch, frozen to death.

45:13.409 --> 45:22.883
Her father was abusive
and she ran away.

45:22.885 --> 45:27.454
She got lost in the
woods in January.

45:27.456 --> 45:30.258
[CROWD CHATTER BEGINS]

45:30.260 --> 45:33.161
At this point we do not have
any people or person of

45:33.163 --> 45:37.798
interest. We've not ruled out
any situation though, and we are

45:37.800 --> 45:40.967
now searching all the known
whereabouts of Halley.

45:40.969 --> 45:43.204
Where she might have gone,
and where she's been.

45:43.206 --> 45:47.909
We will continue the search.
We have all our people on this.

45:47.911 --> 45:50.845
REPORTER: Is there anything the
community can do at this time?

45:50.847 --> 45:53.280
I'll let Detective
Willow take that.

45:53.282 --> 45:55.550
Yes, if anyone has any
information we ask that you

45:55.552 --> 45:58.385
come forward.
Time is of the essence in cases

45:58.387 --> 46:03.192
like this, the more
time that goes by the...

46:03.927 --> 46:06.827
If you have any information
please call our hotline or email

46:06.829 --> 46:10.565
me directly or Detective
Shepherd, and um Mrs. Dawn has

46:10.567 --> 46:17.907
something to say.

46:18.106 --> 46:21.242
I just like to thank
everybody here for your support

46:21.244 --> 46:26.380
in helping find my daughter.

46:26.382 --> 46:32.052
I'm overwhelmed by the
support here today.

46:32.054 --> 46:35.856
And I know that my
daughter wherever she is,

46:35.858 --> 46:38.925
would be touched as well.

46:38.927 --> 46:45.867
If you have any idea, any sorta
idea at all, about where she

46:45.869 --> 46:54.407
might be, a sighting, or a rumor
or anything, please... please

46:54.409 --> 46:57.547
just...

46:58.380 --> 47:06.621
♪ MELANCHOLY MUSIC BEGINS ♪

47:06.623 --> 47:10.458
[BIRDS CHIRPING SOUND EFFECT]

47:10.460 --> 47:14.061
You look good. I'd hire you.

47:14.063 --> 47:19.532
You already did once.

47:19.534 --> 47:23.570
I still don't know why
you want to leave.

47:23.572 --> 47:26.139
Because I want to
work somewhere, where I'm not

47:26.141 --> 47:27.641
miserable all the time.

47:27.643 --> 47:30.043
You're only miserable
all the time when you think

47:30.045 --> 47:33.613
you're miserable all the time.

47:33.615 --> 47:36.083
There's a little
girl missing. Something very bad

47:36.085 --> 47:41.322
happened to her. I don't want
to surround myself with that.

47:41.324 --> 47:42.423
So you want to
